The culture of pride in "good" still exists," he says, adding that modern technology and increasing pressure on the students meant that sleep deprivation was a growing problem.
To ensure that you have enough sleep, of good quality, should be the student's "secret weapon" to combat stress, fatigue and anxiety, he said - even to avoid weight gain because insomnia puts the brain in starvation and makes them constantly hungry.
